# NEXORA AI

# Authentication Implementation Guide

Version: 1.0

Status: Ready for Implementation

---

# 1. Objective

This document defines the complete authentication architecture for the NEXORA AI platform.

Authentication is the foundation of the entire application. Every protected resource, API, and business module depends on this implementation.

The authentication module must provide:

• Secure user registration

• Secure login

• JWT Authentication

• Refresh Token Authentication

• Role Based Access Control (RBAC)

• Email Verification

• Password Reset

• Session Management

• API Security

• Account Status Management

• Audit Logging

The implementation should follow enterprise security standards and be scalable for future integrations such as OAuth2, Google Login, Microsoft Login, LinkedIn Login, and Multi-Factor Authentication.

---

# 2. Scope

This module covers authentication for every user of the platform.

Supported Users

```
Student

Recruiter

College

Administrator
```

Every user authenticates using the same authentication system while receiving permissions according to their assigned role.

---

# 3. Authentication Architecture

```
                    Client Application

                           │

                           ▼

                Authentication Controller

                           │

                           ▼

               Authentication Service Layer

                           │

                           ▼

          Spring Security AuthenticationManager

                           │

                           ▼

                  UserDetailsService

                           │

                           ▼

                    PostgreSQL Database

                           │

                           ▼

                    JWT Token Generator

                           │

                           ▼

                  Authenticated Response
```

The Authentication Controller should never communicate directly with the database.

All requests must pass through the Service Layer.

