# 13. JWT Strategy

Use two different tokens.

Access Token

```
15 Minutes
```

Refresh Token

```
30 Days
```

JWT should include

```
User ID

Email

Role

Issued Time

Expiration Time

Issuer
```

Sensitive information must never be stored inside JWT payloads.

---

# 14. Password Policy

Minimum Length

```
8 Characters
```

Recommended Length

```
12+ Characters
```

Requirements

```
Uppercase

Lowercase

Number

Special Character
```

Example

```
Nexora@2026
```

Passwords must always be encrypted using BCrypt.

---

# 15. Password Encryption

Use

```
BCryptPasswordEncoder
```

Never

```
MD5

SHA1

Plain Text
```

Passwords should never be reversible.

---

# 16. Email Verification

Every newly registered account remains inactive until email verification succeeds.

Verification process

```
Register

↓

Generate Verification Token

↓

Send Email

↓

User Clicks Link

↓

Verify Token

↓

Activate Account
```

---

# 17. Refresh Token Strategy

Refresh tokens should

• Be stored securely

• Be revocable

• Have expiry time

• Rotate after usage

• Be removed after logout

